result.name: Bistro du Vin

reviews.text: Bistro for the French cuisine. Good food, great place, friendly staff, nice decor. Take the Exit C at MTR Kennedy Town Station to Davis street on the waterfront. It is about 6 to 10 mins of walking distance.

When their chef has good tastes and cares about the quality of ingredients, everything they made are delicious. 😋 staffs are friendly and professional. They know so well about everything on the menu and would give you great suggestions whenever you ask. Been there multiple times and always want to go back when i need some treats or impress a friend~ 🥳

***Revised Rating 4/2019*** Sorry guys the chef left for Singapore and the set lunches were not the same. Price went up a little and foods went from excellent to  good. Vey salty. People used to hike over for value lunch, but it wasn't full on a Friday. People were still super nice, but the change was immediately noticed. 

***2017 Rating***You get incredible foods at lunch. Take the MTR and walk a little. My favorite is the oxtail!
Had a Sunday lunch here, comfortable environment and the food was OK, creme brulee was a must try.

Had our first experience with Bistro du Vin on their weekend. We followed the chef’s suggestions and the dinner was superb - especially the Wagu beef. Another “must return” on our Hong Kong list. Highly recommended.

result.name: Bistro du Vin

reviews.text: 呢間性價比超高，我們七個人訂了枱食午餐，呢度下午只做套餐，我們因為人多，所以叫了不同的主菜齊齊分享，環境像法國小店很有氣氛，食物好新鮮，我覺得每個菜都做得非常好，看得出廚師很用心及高水平，很推薦。
食物一般，没有太多驚喜，可惜一支不出名的紐西蘭紅酒收45O是否過份些呢？
